cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.RO, cs.CR 

The paper discusses Cyber-Physical Systems (CPS) and their optimization using formal methods. The most relevant sub-category is cs.SY (Systems and Control) as the paper focuses on the control and monitoring of physical systems using cyber-components. The paper also mentions the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) in optimizing CPS systems. Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of resiliency and redundancy in CPS systems, which falls under the sub-categories of software engineering (cs.SE), robotics (cs.RO), and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
